<subSubSection pageId="53" pageNumber="54" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="53.[151,1436,1286,1889]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1359,1385]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific name refers to the native indigenous group that inhabit the 
<typeStatus box="[1182,1230,1359,1385]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">type</typeStatus>
locality in Juruti, southwestern 
<collectingRegion box="[306,359,1395,1421]" country="Suriname" name="Para" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Pará</collectingRegion>
; noun in apposition.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="53" pageNumber="54" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="53.[151,1436,1286,1889]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,1430,1456]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Females of 
<taxonomicName authority="Rheims &amp; Jäger, 2022" authorityName="Rheims &amp; Jäger" authorityYear="2022" box="[459,625,1431,1457]" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" genus="Meri" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="munduruku" status="spec. nov.">
<emphasis box="[459,625,1431,1457]" italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">M. munduruku</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[632,746,1431,1457]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[632,746,1431,1457]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" rank="species">spec. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
resemble those 
<taxonomicName authority="Rheims &amp; Jäger, 2022" authorityName="Rheims &amp; Jäger" authorityYear="2022" box="[928,1058,1431,1456]" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" genus="Meri" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="arraijan" status="spec. nov.">
<emphasis box="[928,1058,1431,1456]" italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">M. arraijan</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1066,1180,1431,1457]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1066,1180,1431,1457]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" rank="species">spec. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[1195,1351,1431,1457]" captionStart="FIGURES 118–123" captionStartId="36.[151,264,1318,1342]" captionTargetBox="[156,1421,429,1284]" captionTargetId="figure-95@36.[155,1433,417,1294]" captionTargetPageId="36" captionText="FIGURES 118–123. 118–120 Meri aparia spec. nov., female (ex MNHN 2028, holotype) (118 epigyne, 119 vulva, 120 schematic course of internal duct system); 121–123 Meri arraijan spec. nov., female (AMNH, paratype) (121 epigyne, 122 vulva, 123 schematic course of internal duct system). ag—anterior groove; EP—epigynal pocket; ft—first turn of duct system; FD— fertilization duct; GP—glandular projection; LL—lateral lobe; MS—median septum; SP—spermathecae. Scale lines: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6550283" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6550283/files/figure.png" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Figs 121–123</figureCitation>
) by the irregular hexagon shape of the MS, wider than long and widest anteriorly, in the epigyne. They are distinguished from the latter species by the pair of anterior grooves in the epigynal field (
<figureCitation box="[994,1088,1503,1529]" captionStart="FIGURES 208–216" captionStartId="54.[151,264,1743,1767]" captionTargetBox="[155,1418,195,1708]" captionTargetId="figure-23@54.[155,1432,181,1720]" captionTargetPageId="54" captionText="FIGURES 208–216. 208–210 Meri mathani (Simon) comb. nov., female (MNHN 2028, lectotype) (208 epigyne, 209 vulva, 210 schematic course of internal duct system); 211–213 Meri munduruku spec. nov., female (MPEG 30776, holotype) (211 epigyne, 212 vulva 213 schematic course of internal duct system); 214–216 Meri paiaia spec. nov., female (IBSP 167988, holotype) (214 epigyne, 215 vulva, 216 schematic course of internal duct system). EP—epigynal pocket; FD—fertilization duct; ft—first turn of duct system; GP—glandular projection; LL—lateral lobe; MS—median septum; SP—spermathecae. Scale lines: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6550344" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6550344/files/figure.png" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Fig. 211</figureCitation>
) and by the internal ducts with FW dilated (
<figureCitation box="[291,388,1539,1565]" captionStart="FIGURES 208–216" captionStartId="54.[151,264,1743,1767]" captionTargetBox="[155,1418,195,1708]" captionTargetId="figure-23@54.[155,1432,181,1720]" captionTargetPageId="54" captionText="FIGURES 208–216. 208–210 Meri mathani (Simon) comb. nov., female (MNHN 2028, lectotype) (208 epigyne, 209 vulva, 210 schematic course of internal duct system); 211–213 Meri munduruku spec. nov., female (MPEG 30776, holotype) (211 epigyne, 212 vulva 213 schematic course of internal duct system); 214–216 Meri paiaia spec. nov., female (IBSP 167988, holotype) (214 epigyne, 215 vulva, 216 schematic course of internal duct system). EP—epigynal pocket; FD—fertilization duct; ft—first turn of duct system; GP—glandular projection; LL—lateral lobe; MS—median septum; SP—spermathecae. Scale lines: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6550344" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6550344/files/figure.png" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Fig. 212</figureCitation>
) (anterior groove single and FW slender in 
<taxonomicName authority="Rheims &amp; Jäger, 2022" authorityName="Rheims &amp; Jäger" authorityYear="2022" box="[876,1007,1539,1564]" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" genus="Meri" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="arraijan" status="spec. nov.">
<emphasis box="[876,1007,1539,1564]" italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">M. arraijan</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1014,1129,1539,1565]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1014,1129,1539,1565]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" rank="species">spec. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
). Males are unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="53" pageNumber="54" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="53.[151,1436,1286,1889]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,581,1574,1601]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">
Description. Female (
<typeStatus box="[458,568,1574,1600]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">holotype</typeStatus>
):
</emphasis>
Total length 15.7. Prosoma 6.8 long, 6.3 wide. Opisthosoma 8.5 long, 4.7 wide. Eyes: diameters 0.48, 0.42, 0.30, 0.38; interdistances: 0.40, 0.20, 0.65, 0.68, 0.35, 0.26. Legs: I: absent; II: - (8.6, 3.4, 7.8, rest of leg absent); III: 22.4 (6.9, 3.0, 5.5, 5.2, 1.8); IV: 24.3 (7.5, 2.6, 6.0, 6.3, 1.9). Spination (legs III–IV) follows the generic pattern except femur IV: r1-1-1. Epigyne: EF slightly longer than wide; MAB short and narrow; EP triangular, as wide as long, opening at posterior margin of MS; LL touching posteriorly (
<figureCitation box="[1267,1367,1719,1745]" captionStart="FIGURES 208–216" captionStartId="54.[151,264,1743,1767]" captionTargetBox="[155,1418,195,1708]" captionTargetId="figure-23@54.[155,1432,181,1720]" captionTargetPageId="54" captionText="FIGURES 208–216. 208–210 Meri mathani (Simon) comb. nov., female (MNHN 2028, lectotype) (208 epigyne, 209 vulva, 210 schematic course of internal duct system); 211–213 Meri munduruku spec. nov., female (MPEG 30776, holotype) (211 epigyne, 212 vulva 213 schematic course of internal duct system); 214–216 Meri paiaia spec. nov., female (IBSP 167988, holotype) (214 epigyne, 215 vulva, 216 schematic course of internal duct system). EP—epigynal pocket; FD—fertilization duct; ft—first turn of duct system; GP—glandular projection; LL—lateral lobe; MS—median septum; SP—spermathecae. Scale lines: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6550344" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6550344/files/figure.png" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Figs 211</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1378,1424,1719,1745]" captionStart="FIGURES 217–220" captionStartId="55.[151,264,1808,1832]" captionTargetBox="[171,1404,529,1763]" captionTargetId="figure-122@55.[158,1429,525,1785]" captionTargetPageId="55" captionText="FIGURES 217–220. 217–218 Meri munduruku spec. nov., female (MPEG 30776, holotype) (217 epigyne, 218 vulva); 219– 220 Meri paiaia spec. nov., female (IBSP 167988, holotype) (219 epigyne, 220 vulva). Scale lines: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6550346" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6550346/files/figure.png" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">217</figureCitation>
). Vulva: internal ducts with FW mediad; GP longer than wide, anteriad, asrising from ducts at first turn; SP ovoid; FD antero laterad (
<figureCitation box="[319,476,1791,1817]" captionStart="FIGURES 208–216" captionStartId="54.[151,264,1743,1767]" captionTargetBox="[155,1418,195,1708]" captionTargetId="figure-23@54.[155,1432,181,1720]" captionTargetPageId="54" captionText="FIGURES 208–216. 208–210 Meri mathani (Simon) comb. nov., female (MNHN 2028, lectotype) (208 epigyne, 209 vulva, 210 schematic course of internal duct system); 211–213 Meri munduruku spec. nov., female (MPEG 30776, holotype) (211 epigyne, 212 vulva 213 schematic course of internal duct system); 214–216 Meri paiaia spec. nov., female (IBSP 167988, holotype) (214 epigyne, 215 vulva, 216 schematic course of internal duct system). EP—epigynal pocket; FD—fertilization duct; ft—first turn of duct system; GP—glandular projection; LL—lateral lobe; MS—median septum; SP—spermathecae. Scale lines: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6550344" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6550344/files/figure.png" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Figs 212–213</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[488,534,1791,1817]" captionStart="FIGURES 217–220" captionStartId="55.[151,264,1808,1832]" captionTargetBox="[171,1404,529,1763]" captionTargetId="figure-122@55.[158,1429,525,1785]" captionTargetPageId="55" captionText="FIGURES 217–220. 217–218 Meri munduruku spec. nov., female (MPEG 30776, holotype) (217 epigyne, 218 vulva); 219– 220 Meri paiaia spec. nov., female (IBSP 167988, holotype) (219 epigyne, 220 vulva). Scale lines: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6550346" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6550346/files/figure.png" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">218</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
